Reasoning: 
1. cs.GT (Game Theory): The paper is primarily focused on studying two-player general sum repeated finite games and finding the egalitarian bargaining solution (EBS) for the repeated game. This falls under the domain of game theory, making cs.GT the most likely sub-category. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an algorithm to achieve a high-probability regret bound, which involves learning from the rewards generated from an unknown distribution. This makes cs.LG a likely sub-category as well. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper involves developing an algorithm to optimize the rewards in a repeated game, which falls under the domain of AI. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes an algorithm to achieve a high-probability regret bound, which involves designing efficient data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems): The paper deals with a repeated game involving multiple agents, making cs.MA a possible sub-category as well.
